Topics covered in the practical course:
I Introduction: spectrophotometry and titration.
II Photometric methods for protein concentration determination.
III Buffer solutions and pH.
IV Purification of α-amylase with gel filtration chromatography and determination of specific activity.
V Factors that affect the rates of enzymatic reactions. Determination of kinetic parameters.
VI Protein purification with affinity chromatography and analysis with SDS polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of basic methods used in biochemistry.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course, the students are expected: - to be able to use basic labware used in biochemical experiments. - to be familiar with basic methods in biochemistry. - to be able to interpret the results of the experiment and to compose a report.
